Classification validation video clips

Create video clips with overlaid classified events for detection of false positive event bouts

[1]:

from simba.plotting.clf_validator import ClassifierValidationClips

[5]:

#DEFINITIONS

CONFIG_PATH = '/Users/simon/Desktop/envs/troubleshooting/two_black_animals_14bp/project_folder/project_config.ini'
DATA_PATHS = ['/Users/simon/Desktop/envs/troubleshooting/two_black_animals_14bp/project_folder/csv/machine_results/Together_1.csv'] #PATHS TO VIDEO DATA TO CREATE VALIDATION CLIPS FOR
TIME_WINDOW = 10 # Number of seconds before and after the event bout that should be included in the output video.
CLASSIFIER_NAME = 'Attack' #Name of the classifier to create validation videos for.
CLIPS = False # If True, creates individual video file clips for each validation bout.
CONCATENATED_VIDEO = True # If True, creates a single video including all events bouts for each video. Default: False.
HIGHLIGHT_COLOR = (255, 0, 0) # BGR color of text when probability values are above threshold. If None, same as text_clr.
VIDEO_SPEED = 0.5 # FPS rate in relation to original video. E.g., the same as original video if 1.0. Default: 1.0.
TEXT_COLOR = (0, 0, 255) # Color of text overlay in BGR.

[7]:

video_creator = ClassifierValidationClips(config_path=CONFIG_PATH,
                                          data_paths=DATA_PATHS,
                                          window=TIME_WINDOW,
                                          clf_name=CLASSIFIER_NAME,
                                          clips=CLIPS,
                                          concat_video=CONCATENATED_VIDEO,
                                          highlight_clr=HIGHLIGHT_COLOR,
                                          video_speed=VIDEO_SPEED,
                                          text_clr=TEXT_COLOR)
video_creator.run()
